  "notes": "## Angebots-Nachverfolgung (Quote Follow-Up Pipeline) v1\n\n### Overview\nAutomated follow-up email pipeline for unresponded quotes (angebote).\nRuns daily at 09:00 Europe/Berlin.\n\n### Pipeline Steps\n1. **Schedule Trigger**: Daily 09:00 Berlin timezone\n2. **Fetch Open Quotes**: GET from Supabase angebote (status=offen, gueltig_bis >= today)\n3. **Calculate Days**: Computes daysSinceCreated, daysUntilExpiry, followUpStage\n4. **Filter Actionable**: Only process quotes needing follow-up (skip stage != 'skip')\n5. **Deduplication**: Check email_log for recent follow-ups (last 2 days)\n6. **Switch by Stage**: Route to correct email template\n7. **Send Email**: Via Supabase Edge Function (send-email)\n8. **Log**: Insert into email_log for deduplication\n9. **Update Expired**: PATCH angebote status='abgelaufen' for 28+ day quotes\n\n### Follow-Up Stages\n- Day 3 (reminder_1): Friendly check-in, answer questions\n- Day 7 (reminder_2): Urgency, limited capacity, schedule soon\n- Day 14 (reminder_3): Final reminder, days until expiry, offer updated quote\n- Day 28+ (expired): Quote expired, offer new quote\n\n### Setup Required\n1. **Env Vars**: SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY, COMPANY_NAME, PORTAL_URL\n2. **Supabase**: angebote and email_log tables must exist (see supabase-schema.sql)\n3. **Edge Function**: send-email function deployed to Supabase\n4. **Credentials**: Supabase API credential configured in n8n\n\n### Email Branding\n- Dark theme (#09090b bg, #18181b card, #6366f1 accent, #fafafa text)\n- Inline CSS for email client compatibility\n- All text in German, professional tone\n- Portal link for self-service"
